    <h2 id="practice-strategy">Practice Strategy</h2>
    <p><strong>Learn radicals alongside characters.</strong> When you learn a new character, identify its radical. This creates mental connections that reinforce both.</p>
    <p><strong>Group characters by radical.</strong> Study all the "water" characters together, then all the "heart" characters. This highlights the patterns.</p>
    <p><strong>Practice writing radicals.</strong> Get comfortable writing each radical form so that complex characters become combinations of easy parts. Our <a href="/chinese/tools/stroke-order/">Stroke Order tool</a> shows the correct way to write basic characters.</p>
